SIMPLE: arsenious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arsenious
<hw>Ar*se"ni*ous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ars⟦eacute⟧nieux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to,
consisting of, or containing, arsenic; <as>as, <ex>arsenious</ex> powder
or glass</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or derived from,
arsenic, when having an equivalence next lower than the highest; <as>as,
<ex>arsenious</ex> acid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arsenite</ent>⟦br⟧
